'''Nathanaël Mbuku Wa Mbuku''' (born 16 March 2002) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for {{French football updater|Montpellier}} club [[Montpellier HSC|Montpellier]], on loan from [[Bundesliga]] club [[FC Augsburg]]. Born in France, he plays for the [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo national team]].

==Club career==

===Reims===
On 23 November 2018, Mbuku signed his first professional contract with [[Stade de Reims]] for three years.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.actufoot.com/75/nathanael-mbuku-a-signe-professionnel-stade-de-reims|title=Nathanaël Mbuku a signé professionnel au Stade de Reims|date=23 November 2018}}</ref> He made his professional debut with Reims in a 2–0 [[Ligue 1]] win over [[Olympique de Marseille]] on 10 August 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.soccerway.com/matches/2019/08/10/france/ligue-1/olympique-de-marseille/stade-de-reims/3030548/?ICID=HP_MS_02_01|title=Olympique Marseille vs. Reims - 10 August 2019 - Soccerway|website=www.soccerway.com}}</ref>

He scored his first goal in [[Ligue 1]] in a 4–0 win against [[Montpellier HSC|Montpellier]] on 25 October 2020, from an "acrobatic kick".<ref>{{cite news |last1=Lampin |first1=Julien |last2=Audabram |first2=Alexandre |title=Ligue 1 (J8) {{!}} Le Stade de Reims cartonne à Montpellier (4-0) et valide son premier succès en championnat |url=https://www.francebleu.fr/sports/football/ligue-1-j8-le-stade-de-reims-cartonne-a-montpellier-4-0-et-valide-son-premier-succes-en-l1-cette-1603645967 |accessdate=26 October 2020 |work=France Bleu |date=25 October 2020 |language=French}}</ref> His teammate [[Boulaye Dia]] also scored from a penalty after Mbuku was fouled. The win was Reims' first in the league in the [[2020–21 Stade de Reims season|2020–21 season]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Reims stun Montpellier, Briand scores 100th goal |url=https://www.ligue1.com/Articles/MATCH-REPORTS/2020/10/25/reims-stun-montpellier-briand-scores-100th-goal |website=Ligue 1 |accessdate=26 October 2020 |date=25 October 2020}}</ref>

===FC Augsburg===
On 30 January 2023, Mbuku signed a four-and-a-half-year contract with [[FC Augsburg]] in German [[Bundesliga]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=FC Augsburg|url=https://www.fcaugsburg.de/en/article/fca-sign-nathanael-mbuku-from-stade-de-reims-17242|title=FCA sign Nathanaël Mbuku from Stade de Reims|date=30 January 2023|access-date=30 January 2023}}</ref>

In January 2024, he joined [[Ligue 2]] club [[AS Saint-Étienne|Saint-Étienne]] on loan for the remainder of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.asse.fr/fr/actualites/nathanael-mbuku-s-engage-avec-les-verts-ac35898|trans-title=Nathanaël Mbuku joins the Greens|title=Nathanaël Mbuku s'engage avec les Verts|language=French|website=www.asse.fr|date=21 January 2024|accessdate=22 January 2024}}</ref>

===Dinamo Zagreb===
On 3 September 2024, Mbuku signed a multi-year contract with [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]] in Croatia.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Dinamo Zagreb|url=https://gnkdinamo.hr/hr/vijesti/clanak/nathanal-mbuku-novi-igrac-dinama|title=Nathanaël Mbuku novi igrač Dinama|trans-title=Nathanaël Mbuku is a new Dinamo player|date=3 September 2024|access-date=4 September 2024|language=hr}}</ref> Augsburg reserved an option to buy him back at the end of the 2024–25 season.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=FC Augsburg|url=https://www.fcaugsburg.de/en/article/nathanael-mbuku-moves-to-dinamo-zagreb-20748|title=Nathanaël Mbuku moves to Dinamo Zagreb|date=3 September 2024|access-date=4 September 2024}}</ref>

===Montpellier===
In July 2025, Augsburg bought him back and Mbuku moved to [[Montpellier HSC|Montpellier]] in France on loan with an option to buy.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Montpellier HSC|url=https://mhscfoot.com/articles/2025-2026/transfert/nathanael-mbuku-rejoint-le-mhsc/|title=Nathanaël Mbuku rejoint le MHSC|trans-title=Nathanaël Mbuku joins the MHSC|date=8 July 2025|access-date=12 July 2025|language=fr}}</ref>

==International career==
With the [[France national under-17 football team|France U-17 national team]], Mbuku took part in the [[UEFA European Under-17 Championship]] held in [[Ireland]]. He featured in five matches during the tournament. He made an impact by scoring a goal against the [[Netherlands national under-17 football team|Netherlands]] in the group stage, and later provided an assist in the semi-final against [[Italy national under-17 football team|Italy]], which ended in a 1–2 defeat.

A few months later, he participated in the [[2019 FIFA U-17 World Cup]] in [[Brazil]]. During the tournament, he again played five matches. He stood out by scoring a hat-trick in the Round of 16 against [[Australia national under-17 football team|Australia]]. In the quarter-final against [[Spain national under-17 football team|Spain]], he contributed with a goal and an assist. He scored once more in the semi-final against the host nation, [[Brazil national under-17 football team|Brazil]]. France eventually won the bronze medal by defeating the [[Netherlands national under-17 football team|Netherlands]] in the third-place playoff on 17 November 2019.<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2020-02-16 |language=fr-FR |last1=FIFA.com |title=Coupe du Monde U-17 de la FIFA 2019 - Infos - La France se console avec le bronze (1-3) - FIFA.com |url=https://fr.fifa.com/u17worldcup/news/la-france-se-console-avec-le-bronze-1-3 |website=www.fifa.com}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref> Individually, Mbuku was awarded the Adidas Silver Boot as the tournament’s second-highest goalscorer.<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2020-02-17 |language=fr-FR |last1=FIFA.com |title=Coupe du Monde U-17 de la FIFA 2019 - Infos - Récompenses et consolations en or - FIFA.com |url=https://fr.fifa.com/u17worldcup/news/recompenses-et-consolations-en-or-x2389 |website=www.fifa.com}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

On 2 July 2021, he was named in the 21-man squad selected by Sylvain Ripoll to represent France at the [[Football at the 2020 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|2020 Summer Olympics]], held in [[Japan]] in summer 2021.<ref>{{cite web|author=Dahbia Hattabi |date=2 July 2021 |title=Jeux Olympiques : la liste finale de la France |url=https://www.footmercato.net/a8741212751515549464-jeux-olympiques-la-liste-finale-de-la-france |website=footmercato.net}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref> He made his debut for the [[France Olympic football team|France Olympic team]] on 16 July, coming on as a substitute for [[Arnaud Nordin]] in the 69th minute of a friendly match against [[South Korea national under-23 football team|South Korea]]. Mbuku scored the winning goal late in the game, securing a 2–1 victory.<ref>{{cite web|author=Richard Loyant |date=16 July 2021 |title=Beau succès sur la Corée du Sud (2-1) |url=https://www.fff.fr/article/3170-beau-succes-sur-la-coree-du-sud-2-1-.html |website=fff.fr}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

In August 2024, he changed his sporting nationality and received his first call-up to the [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo national team]] for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualification]] against [[Guinea national football team|Guinea]] on 6 September and [[Ethiopia national football team|Ethiopia]] on 9 September.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fcaugsburg.de/en/article/12-players-called-up-for-international-duty-20735 |title=12 players called up for international duty |date=2024-09-02 |language=en |website=fcaugsburg.de |publisher=FC Augsburg |access-date=2024-09-04 |archive-date=2024-09-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240904095342/https://www.fcaugsburg.de/en/article/12-players-called-up-for-international-duty-20735 |url-status=live}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Born in France, Mbuku holds French and Congolese nationalities.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Nathanaël MBUKU |url=https://www.unfp.org/joueur/nathanael-mbuku-22462/ |access-date=9 January 2024 |website=unfp.org |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://voila.cd/foot-france-u17-decouvrez-06-internationaux-francais-dorigine-congolaise/|title=VOILA NIGHT - FOOT-FRANCE U17: DÉCOUVREZ 06 INTERNATIONAUX FRANÇAIS D'ORIGINE CONGOLAISE}}</ref>

